# map-ops

Associative-collection churn: `Map.updated` + `getOrElse` in a 500-iter loop
over a 100-key keyspace. Stresses the immutable `Map` data structure (hashing,
copy-on-update) — a path no List/Array workload covers.

```scalascript
def workload(): Long =
  var m: Map[Int, Int] = Map[Int, Int]()
  var sum = 0L
  var i = 0
  while i < 500 do
    m = m.updated(i % 100, i)
    sum = sum + m.getOrElse(i % 100, 0).toLong
    i = i + 1
  sum
```
